DOS-PORT (patch 0083, Phase 9 wave 17.4 bundle).

Bug: TextBox::DrawFrame's three drawSpriteChopped calls passed
alpha=210 (semi-transparent). In INDEX8 mode (wave 16 default)
this falls through both fast paths:

- _try_fast_blit (Renderer.cpp): alpha!=255 gate rejects.
- _try_fast_blit_alpha (Renderer.cpp): RGB565-only — no INDEX8
  sibling exists in the wave-12.5 lever-B implementation.

Both fast paths miss → SDL_RenderTexture is called → SDL3 drops the
colorkey when blending alpha onto INDEX8 → transparent pixels around
the sawtooth-triangle decorations on the menu/dialog frame render
as opaque black on real HW ("menu black-boxes" bug, diagnosed by
the menu-debug agent and documented at
memory/sdl3_index8_alpha_colorkey_bug.md).

Cheap fix this patch ships: change alpha=210 → alpha=255 at the
three drawSpriteChopped sites in TextBox::DrawFrame. The fast path
now engages (alpha==255 takes the opaque _try_fast_blit branch which
honors colorkey correctly), bug goes away. Loses cosmetic semi-
transparency on the menu / dialog frame.

The proper fix (a new _blit_indexed_alpha primitive mirroring
wave-12.5's _blit_rgb565_alpha) is queued as a polish-backlog item;
it's not on the fps critical path and shipping the cheap fix
unblocks visual correctness now.

3-line content change. Comment block added on the function explains
the rationale so future readers don't "restore" the 210 alpha not
realizing it triggers the bug.
---
 src/TextBox/TextBox.cpp | 21 ++++++++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/TextBox/TextBox.cpp b/src/TextBox/TextBox.cpp
index 74449ab..0ef8f01 100644
--- a/src/TextBox/TextBox.cpp
+++ b/src/TextBox/TextBox.cpp
@@ -530,16 +530,31 @@ void c------------------------------() {}
 
 // draws the frame of an empty text box spanning
 // the specified coordinates.
+//
+// DOS-PORT (patch 0083, Phase 9 wave 17.4 bundle): alpha was 210
+// (semi-transparent) on all three drawSpriteChopped calls. In INDEX8
+// mode (wave 16 default) that alpha value triggers a fall-through:
+// `_try_fast_blit` rejects on alpha != 255 (gate at L2862), and
+// `_try_fast_blit_alpha` is RGB565-only (no INDEX8 sibling — see
+// memory/sdl3_index8_alpha_colorkey_bug.md). Both fast paths miss →
+// SDL_RenderTexture is called → SDL3 drops the colorkey when blending
+// alpha onto INDEX8 → transparent pixels around the sawtooth-triangle
+// decorations render as opaque black ("menu black-boxes" bug).
+//
+// Cheap fix: alpha=255. Loses cosmetic semi-transparency on menu and
+// dialog boxes. Real fix (a new `_blit_indexed_alpha` primitive
+// mirroring wave-12.5's `_blit_rgb565_alpha`) is queued as polish-
+// backlog item; it's not on the fps critical path.
 void TextBox::DrawFrame(int x, int y, int w, int h)
 {
-  Renderer::getInstance()->sprites.drawSpriteChopped(x, y, SPR_TEXTBOX, 0, w, 8, 210); // draw top
+  Renderer::getInstance()->sprites.drawSpriteChopped(x, y, SPR_TEXTBOX, 0, w, 8, 255); // draw top
   y += 8;
 
   for (int draw = 0; draw < h - 16; draw += 8)
   {
-    Renderer::getInstance()->sprites.drawSpriteChopped(x, y, SPR_TEXTBOX, 1, w, 8, 210); // draw middle
+    Renderer::getInstance()->sprites.drawSpriteChopped(x, y, SPR_TEXTBOX, 1, w, 8, 255); // draw middle
     y += 8;
   }
 
-  Renderer::getInstance()->sprites.drawSpriteChopped(x, y, SPR_TEXTBOX, 2, w, 8, 210); // draw bottom
+  Renderer::getInstance()->sprites.drawSpriteChopped(x, y, SPR_TEXTBOX, 2, w, 8, 255); // draw bottom
 }
